  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of In-line Chlorinator Technology as a water treatment solution for B</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following some preliminary tests and analysis of this inline chlorination technology by Oxfam, they is now a need to formally engage the National Coordination Unit to work with the National Institute of Health Research (NIHR) to evaluate the inline chlorinator and its subsequent adoption as a solution for borehole water treatment in cholera/typhoid hot spots in Zimbabwe. This project is therefore aimed at 1.Getting the inline chlorinator technology approved as a water treatment technology for B Type Bush Pumps used in cholera/typhoid hot spot areas in Zimbabwe by the National Coordination Unit (NCU) through the Sustainability Subcommittee (SS). 2.If approved, advocate for the large -scale adoption of the inline chlorinators in Harare and other cholera/typhoid hot spot areas in Zimbabwe by local governments, urban councils and other partners.</narrative>
  </description>
